Calibration - Class in org.eclipse.nvplayout.model
Calibration is the global model for the calibration view.
This model contain the global configuration, i-e : Number of block present in calibration. The start address of the calibration memory section. The reference of the different memory block.
Calibration(long) - Constructor for class org.eclipse.nvplayout.model.Calibration
Set a global structure of calibration memory.

CalibrationBlock - Class in org.eclipse.nvplayout.model
CalibrationBlock is the first layer of the model.
This model contain the definition of a memory block, i-e : Name of block. The start address of the block. The ID of the block. The number of variable in the block. The memory size of the block. The reference of the different variable.
CalibrationBlock() - Constructor for class org.eclipse.nvplayout.model.CalibrationBlock
Set a global memory block structure.
The number of variable in 1 block is limited to 100.

CalibrationVariable - Class in org.eclipse.nvplayout.model
CalibrationVariable is the last layer of the model.
This model contain the definition of a variable block, i-e : Alias in RAM. The address of the variable. The value of the variable in decimal. The Type of variable (uint8, sint8, uint16, ...). The size of the variable, link to the type.
CalibrationVariable() - Constructor for class org.eclipse.nvplayout.model.CalibrationVariable
Set a global variable structure.
The initialization of the variable correspond to an unsigned char named New Variable set at 0.
